  "exercises": "<div class=\"pt-6 font-sans\">\n    <!-- Lesson Title -->\n    <div class=\"text-center px-4 mb-12\">\n        <h1 class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-gray-800\">Lesson 11: Practice Exercises</h1>\n        <p class=\"mt-2 text-lg text-sky-600 font-medium\">Let's master the universal square root finder!</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Exercise 1 -->\n    <div class=\"exercise-container max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 mb-8\">\n        <h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2\">Exercise 1: Diameter and Radius</h3>\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4\">You are asked to represent √4.5 on the number line. What would be the length of the diameter and the radius of the semicircle you must construct?</p>\n        <button class=\"show-answer-button mt-4 bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-600 transition duration-300\">Show Answer</button>\n        <div class=\"answer-container mt-4 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg\">\n            <h4 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2\">Calculating the Dimensions:</h4>\n            <div class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 1: Find the diameter.</strong> The diameter is always the length x + 1.</p>\n                <p class=\"font-mono text-lg ml-6 mt-1 text-gray-700\">Diameter = 4.5 + 1 = 5.5 units.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2 mt-2\"><strong>Step 2: Find the radius.</strong> The radius is always half of the diameter.</p>\n                <p class=\"font-mono text-lg ml-6 mt-1 text-gray-700\">Radius = 5.5 / 2 = 2.75 units.</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 font-bold text-lg text-green-600\">Final Answer: Diameter = 5.5 units, Radius = 2.75 units.</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <!-- Exercise 2 -->\n    <div class=\"exercise-container max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 mb-8\">\n        <h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2\">Exercise 2: Working Backwards</h3>\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4\">In a geometric construction, the diameter of the semicircle drawn is 10 units. What irrational number (√x) is this construction designed to find?</p>\n        <button class=\"show-answer-button mt-4 bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-600 transition duration-300\">Show Answer</button>\n        <div class=\"answer-container mt-4 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg\">\n            <h4 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2\">Finding 'x':</h4>\n            <div class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 1:</strong> We know the formula for the diameter is x + 1.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 2:</strong> We are given that the diameter is 10. So, we can set up the equation: x + 1 = 10.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 3:</strong> Solve for x by subtracting 1 from both sides.</p>\n                <p class=\"font-mono text-lg ml-6 mt-1 text-gray-700\">x = 10 - 1 = 9</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2 mt-2\"><strong>Step 4:</strong> The construction is designed to find √x.</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 font-bold text-lg text-green-600\">Final Answer: The construction is designed to find √9 (which is 3).</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Exercise 3 -->\n    <div class=\"exercise-container max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 mb-8\">\n        <h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2\">Exercise 3: Identifying the Final Step</h3>\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4\">After constructing the perpendicular line BD of length √x as shown below, what is the final action required to locate √x on the number line?</p>\n        <div class=\"flex justify-center my-4\">\n            <svg viewBox=\"0 0 500 300\" class=\"w-full\">\n                <line x1=\"50\" y1=\"280\" x2=\"450\" y2=\"280\" stroke=\"#4b5563\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n                <path d=\"M100 280 A 150 150 0 0 1 400 280\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6b7280\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/>\n                <line x1=\"300\" y1=\"280\" x2=\"300\" y2=\"130\" stroke=\"#16a34a\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n                <text x=\"310\" y=\"200\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#16a34a\">√x</text>\n                <text x=\"295\" y=\"125\" font-size=\"12\">D</text>\n                <text x=\"300\" y=\"270\" font-size=\"12\">B(0)</text>\n            </svg>\n        </div>\n        <button class=\"show-answer-button mt-4 bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-600 transition duration-300\">Show Answer</button>\n        <div class=\"answer-container mt-4 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg\">\n            <h4 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2\">The Final Action:</h4>\n            <div class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">\n                <p class=\"mb-2\">The line segment BD gives us the correct <span class=\"font-semibold\">length</span>, but it's not yet on the number line itself.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\">The final step is to transfer this length onto the number line.</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 font-bold text-lg text-green-600\">Final Answer: Using a compass, place the point at B (the origin) and the pencil at D, then swing an arc down to intersect the number line. That intersection point is √x.</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <!-- Exercise 4 -->\n    <div class=\"exercise-container max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 mb-8\">\n        <h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2\">Exercise 4: True or False</h3>\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4\">When finding √x, the perpendicular line is always drawn from the midpoint of the diameter AC.</p>\n        <button class=\"show-answer-button mt-4 bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-600 transition duration-300\">Show Answer</button>\n        <div class=\"answer-container mt-4 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg\">\n            <h4 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2\">Checking the Method:</h4>\n            <div class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">\n                <p class=\"mb-2\">Let's review the steps. The line segment is marked as A-B (length x) and B-C (length 1).</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\">The midpoint (O) is used as the <span class=\"font-semibold\">center of the semicircle</span>.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\">The perpendicular line that gives us the length √x is always drawn from <span class=\"font-semibold\">Point B</span>, which is the point separating the 'x' segment and the '1' segment.</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 font-bold text-lg text-red-600\">Final Answer: False.</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <!-- Exercise 5 -->\n    <div class=\"exercise-container max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 mb-8\">\n        <h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2\">Exercise 5: What is 'x'?</h3>\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4\">A student correctly constructs the diagram below and finds that the length of the perpendicular BD is 3 units. What was the original value of 'x' (the length of AB) they were trying to find the square root of?</p>\n         <div class=\"flex justify-center my-4\">\n             <svg viewBox=\"0 0 500 300\" class=\"w-full\">\n                <line x1=\"50\" y1=\"280\" x2=\"450\" y2=\"280\" stroke=\"#4b5563\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n                <path d=\"M50 280 A 200 200 0 0 1 450 280\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6b7280\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/>\n                <line x1=\"150\" y1=\"280\" x2=\"150\" y2=\"80\" stroke=\"#16a34a\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n                <text x=\"160\" y=\"180\" font-size=\"16\" fill=\"#16a34a\">3 units</text>\n                <text x=\"50\" y=\"270\" font-size=\"12\">A</text>\n                <text x=\"150\" y=\"270\" font-size=\"12\">B</text>\n                <text x=\"450\" y=\"270\" font-size=\"12\">C</text>\n                <text x=\"145\" y=\"75\" font-size=\"12\">D</text>\n            </svg>\n        </div>\n        <button class=\"show-answer-button mt-4 bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-600 transition duration-300\">Show Answer</button>\n        <div class=\"answer-container mt-4 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg\">\n            <h4 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2\">Finding the Original 'x':</h4>\n            <div class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 1:</strong> The length of the perpendicular line in this construction is always equal to √x.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 2:</strong> We are given that the length of this line (BD) is 3.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 3:</strong> Therefore, we can set up the equation: √x = 3.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 4:</strong> To find x, we square both sides of the equation: (√x)² = 3².</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 font-bold text-lg text-green-600\">Final Answer: The original value of x was 9.</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n</div>\n<!--end-of-code-block-->",
